    "description": {
      "en": {
        "provenance": "imported",
        "value": "A total of 22 government schools (Lower Secondary -6, Secondary- 6 and Higher Secondary-10) of young people, mainly school children will get the opportunity to take active roles in raising climate and disaster awareness.\r\n\t\r\n\t\t10 most active students from each school (6 girls and 4 boys) will take a leadership role in climate change and disaster management activities.\r\n\t\r\n\t\tA total of 330 teachers (20% females and 80% males) will learn about climate change disaster and its integration/extension into/of different subjects\r\n\t\r\n\t\t\r\n\t\t\tA total of 4400 students (50% girls and 50% boys) from classes 6 to 9 will participate in climate and disaster literacy and research activities.\r\n\t\r\n\t\r\n\t\t\r\n\t\t\tA total of 242 members from school management committees (25% females and 75% males) will be sensitized on climate change and disaster.\r\n\t\r\n\t\r\n\t\t\r\n\t\t\tAt least 11000 farmers (60% females and 40% males) from 2750 households will receive climate change and disaster management knowledge"
      },
      "ne": null
    },
